# Normalize line endings to LF on checkout, on every OS.
#
# Why: this is a cross-platform Node/TS repo. With Git's `core.autocrlf=true`
# (the default on the GitHub windows-latest runner and many Windows dev boxes),
# LF blobs are checked out as CRLF — and CRLF tripped Node/vitest parsing of a
# source file on Windows CI ("SyntaxError: Invalid or unexpected token", the file
# failing to collect) while passing on macOS/Linux and on LF working trees. Shell
# scripts (.husky hooks, *.sh) also require LF. All blobs are already LF in the
# index, so this only enforces checkout EOL — it does not rewrite history.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows PowerShell installer is the one file we keep CRLF.
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Binary assets — never touch their bytes.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.db binary
*.wasm binary
